dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived 1-m DEM (m) for Trempealeau County, WI 2014
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived digital elevation model for Trempealeau County, Wisconsin in 2014. The dataset is in WTM coordinates(EPSG 3071), with elevation in meters. A DEM represents the bare-Earth surface, removing all natural and built features.
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Administration - Geographic Information Office
uw_supplemental_s: This lidar data dataset was created by the WisconsinView Partners (WVP) – the WI Department of Administration’s Geographic Information Office in collaboration with the UW-Madison Space Science and Engineering Center’s (SSEC) WisconsinView repository. Original lidar data in tiled format from federal or local county/city lidar projects were used to create countywide mosaics of datasets such as DEMS, Intensity images, and DSMs in various projections and coordinate systems. For detailed metadata please visit: https://web.s3.wisc.edu/wsco-wisconsinview/lidar/Trempealeau/Trempealeau_2014_County_Delivery/Metadata/Metadata.zip
